item.itemvalue: JavaScript Debug.Node Server + Angular Client JavaScript

task.summary: Added some rudimentary 3D rotation to the board.
Better 3D + modularization of 3D rotation into its own directive.
Removed custom patched versions of jquery and lodash. Too many other libraries depend on the global variables. :-(
Cleaned up directive dependencies a bit.
Completely refactored the treemap and treemap-tile code, ready for arbitrary layout algorithms.
Switched to a 'need-to-know' interface for the layout engine, which now has access only to 'importance' and 'reposition'.
Made the layout engine independent from tile spacing.
Cleaned up the module and Angular service architecture; got rid of some potentially confusing conventions.
Cleaned up the module and Angular service architecture. Got rid of some potentially confusing conventions. Now auto-generating log message for each module loaded by RequireJS.
Arbitrary tiling with nested tiling layouts. Controls for full-sizing a tile.
Proper icon buttons for maximizing treemap tiles.
Now able to populate the treemap with the actual data from the FMA. But the code has become rather messy now. It's time for some refactoring.
Partway through implementing the connection graph on top of the treemap.
Tried to make d3 graphs on top of the circuitboard work. No luck so far.
